🔥 🎯 8. Pods scaled but NO traffic distribution
## 🧠 Problem
Pods are created, but traffic is not reaching them.

## 🔥 Ideal Answer

> “If pods are scaled but not receiving traffic, I would first check whether the service is correctly routing traffic to all pods.”

## 🔹 Steps

### 🟢 1. Check Service selector (MOST COMMON)
```bash
kubectl get svc
kubectl describe svc
``
* Selector matches pod labels?
---
### 🔵 2. Check Endpoints
```bash
kubectl get endpoints <service>
```
👉 If new pods not listed:
> Service not routing to them
---
### 🟣 3. Readiness Probe
👉 VERY IMPORTANT
* Pods not “Ready” → no traffic
---
### 🟡 4. Load imbalance
* One pod overloaded
* Others idle
---
### 🔴 5. Sticky sessions
* Session affinity enabled
* Same pod serving all requests
---
## 🔥 Final line
> “Most commonly this happens due to selector mismatch or readiness probe failure.”
