# 🔥 🎯 9. Pod stuck in Terminating
## 🧠 Problem
Pod not getting deleted.
---
## 🔥 Ideal Answer
> “If a pod is stuck in Terminating, I would check if there are finalizers or if the container is not shutting down gracefully.”
---
## 🔹 Steps
### 🟢 1. Check finalizers
```bash
kubectl get pod <pod> -o yaml
```
👉 If present:
> Blocking deletion
---
### 🔵 2. Check graceful shutdown
* App not exiting
* PreStop hook stuck
---
### 🟣 3. Check node issue
* Node unreachable
* Kubelet not responding
---
### 🟡 4. Force delete (last option)
```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod> --force --grace-period=0
```
---
##🔥 Final line
> “Common causes are finalizers, stuck processes, or node issues.”
